@xuchuanyin With `DEFERED REBUILD` syntax, it means the datamap loading will be lazy. If there are new load to the fact table, this datamap will be disabled until user trigger `REBUILD DATAMAP`.
For index datamap like lucene and bloom, `REBUILD DATAMAP` will rebuild the datamap incrementally, meaning that if the segment already has datamap data in it, it will not rebuild the datamap for that segment.
